[THUNDER]

2
00:00:24,367 --> 00:00:26,667
[SHOVEL DIGGING]

3
00:02:20,033 --> 00:02:21,434
JESUS CHRIST!

4
00:02:33,501 --> 00:02:35,968
DISPATCH,
THIS IS ADAM DAVID 5.

5
00:02:35,968 --> 00:02:37,467
REQUESTING
WANTS AND WARRANTS

6
00:02:37,467 --> 00:02:40,100
ON A CORAL AND WHITE
FORD COUPE.

7
00:02:40,100 --> 00:02:45,234
FLORIDA LICENSE PLATE
G-S-Q-7-4-K.

8
00:02:45,234 --> 00:02:46,200
OVER.

9
00:02:46,200 --> 00:02:48,701
ROGER, ADAM DAVID 5.
STAND BY.

10
00:03:00,567 --> 00:03:02,601
[GRUNTING]

11
00:03:18,133 --> 00:03:23,367
ADAM DAVID 5, NO WANTS
OR WARRANTS ON GSQ74K.

12
00:03:23,367 --> 00:03:26,534
CAR'S REGISTERED
TO A VINCENT GOTTO.

13
00:03:26,534 --> 00:03:28,200
ROGER, DISPATCH.

14
00:03:50,534 --> 00:03:52,300
[THUNDER]

15
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:25,267
DON'T MOVE!

16
00:05:30,367 --> 00:05:31,767
DROP THE SHOVEL!

17
00:05:35,300 --> 00:05:38,501
I SAID DROP
THE FUCKIN' SHOVEL!

18
00:05:46,501 --> 00:05:48,367
NOW TURN AROUND SLOWLY.

19
00:06:21,167 --> 00:06:23,067
YOU DID A NICE JOB HERE.

20
00:06:23,067 --> 00:06:24,200
THANK YOU, SIR.

21
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:27,167
IT'S A GOOD THING
YOU FOUND HIM WHEN YOU DID.

22
00:06:27,167 --> 00:06:31,434
A COUPLE OF DAYS, THAT WATER TABLE
WOULD HAVE REALLY BLOATED HIM UP.

23
00:06:36,501 --> 00:06:38,634
I'VE GOT SOMETHING HERE.

24
00:06:38,634 --> 00:06:40,667
OH, CHRIST. ANOTHER ONE?

25
00:06:42,868 --> 00:06:46,300
LISTEN, YOU GO BACK
AND GET FORENSICS, O.K.?

26
00:06:46,300 --> 00:06:48,100
YES, SIR.

27
00:06:49,767 --> 00:06:52,067
LET'S GET IT OUT.

28
00:06:52,067 --> 00:06:53,467
EASY.

29
00:06:59,100 --> 00:07:00,667
WHAT THE HELL--

30
00:07:00,667 --> 00:07:03,033
WHAT THE HELL IS THAT?

31
00:07:03,033 --> 00:07:04,501
WHAT IS THAT?

32
00:07:04,501 --> 00:07:06,834
WHAT THE HELL HAVE WE
GOT HERE, HUH?

33
00:07:20,667 --> 00:07:23,133
O.K., TOMMY, ON 3.

34
00:07:23,133 --> 00:07:25,267
1, 2, 3.

35
00:07:25,267 --> 00:07:26,701
LOCAL WOOD SCULPTOR

36
00:07:26,701 --> 00:07:29,234
AND CONVICTED SERIAL
KILLER VINCENT GOTTO

37
00:07:29,234 --> 00:07:31,200
IS IN THE NEWS
ONCE MORE.

38
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:34,367
WITH HIS NEW EXECUTION
DATE LESS THAN A WEEK AWAY,

39
00:07:34,367 --> 00:07:37,300
HIS ATTORNEY HAS FILED
FOR A COMMUTED SENTENCE

40
00:07:37,300 --> 00:07:38,701
WITH THE STATE COURT
OF APPEALS,

41
00:07:38,701 --> 00:07:41,334
AND HIS FUTURE IS
BEING DECIDED NOW

42
00:07:41,334 --> 00:07:43,467
IN THIS VERY COURTHOUSE.

43
00:07:44,667 --> 00:07:48,200
UH, YOUR HONOR, IF MS.
GARRICK HAS SOME NEW EVIDENCE

44
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:50,534
SHE WISHES TO SHARE
WITH THIS COURT,

45
00:07:50,534 --> 00:07:53,033
THE PEOPLE WILL BE MORE
THAN HAPPY TO REVIEW IT.

46
00:07:53,033 --> 00:07:55,701
DO YOU HAVE NEW EVIDENCE,
COUNSELOR?

47
00:07:55,701 --> 00:07:57,634
WELL, NOT EXACTLY,
YOUR HONOR.

48
00:07:57,634 --> 00:08:00,901
I'M AFRAID MY CLIENT IS
NOTORIOUSLY UNCOOPERATIVE,

49
00:08:00,901 --> 00:08:04,734
BUT WHILE REVIEWING THE
ORIGINAL INVESTIGATOR'S NOTES,

50
00:08:04,734 --> 00:08:07,033
I DISCOVERED
SEVERAL DISCREPANCIES.

51
00:08:07,033 --> 00:08:09,033
I BELIEVE,
IF GIVEN ENOUGH TIME,

52
00:08:09,033 --> 00:08:10,767
I CAN ACCOUNT FOR
MY CLIENT'S WHEREABOUTS

53
00:08:10,767 --> 00:08:13,067
DURING AT LEAST TWO OF
THE ALLEGED HOMICIDES.

54
00:08:13,067 --> 00:08:16,901
BUT YOUR CLIENT WAS NEVER CONVICTED
FOR EITHER OF THESE CRIMES, WAS HE?

55
00:08:16,901 --> 00:08:18,501
UH, NO, YOUR HONOR,
HE WASN'T.

56
00:08:18,501 --> 00:08:19,667
HE WASN'T EVEN CHARGED.

57
00:08:19,667 --> 00:08:22,634
HE WAS CHARGED AND CONVICTED
OF ONLY ONE MURDER.

58
00:08:22,634 --> 00:08:25,100
THE MURDER OF HIS OWN SON.

59
00:08:25,100 --> 00:08:28,133
MS. GARRICK HAS THROWN UP
AN ELABORATE SMOKE SCREEN

60
00:08:28,133 --> 00:08:29,667
AT THE PEOPLE'S EXPENSE.

61
00:08:29,667 --> 00:08:31,067
YOUR HONOR, I OBJECT

62
00:08:31,067 --> 00:08:33,300
TO MR. SILVERMAN'S
IMPLICATION AND ATTITUDE.

63
00:08:33,300 --> 00:08:36,234
BUT HIS ARGUMENT
IS NOT WITHOUT MERIT.

64
00:08:36,234 --> 00:08:39,767
AN ALIBI FOR A MURDER THAT YOUR
CLIENT WAS NEVER CHARGED WITH

65
00:08:39,767 --> 00:08:41,834
IS NOT VALID GROUNDS
FOR AN APPEAL.

66
00:08:41,834 --> 00:08:45,367
BUT JUDGE OLSON REFERRED TO THE
OTHER HOMICIDES DURING SENTENCING,

67
00:08:45,367 --> 00:08:48,567
SO EVEN THOUGH MY CLIENT WAS
NEVER TRIED AS A SERIAL KILLER,

68
00:08:48,567 --> 00:08:51,133
HE WAS CONVICTED
AND SENTENCED AS ONE.

69
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:24,901
OH, GOD.

70
00:09:42,801 --> 00:09:45,167
ZOE,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING UP?

71
00:09:45,167 --> 00:09:47,868
ARE THEY ALL DEAD?

72
00:09:47,868 --> 00:09:50,767
ALL RIGHT.
COME ON, YOUNG LADY.

73
00:09:50,767 --> 00:09:52,901
BACK TO BED.

74
00:09:57,834 --> 00:10:00,267
ALL RIGHT. ARE YOU
ALL SETTLED IN NOW?

75
00:10:00,267 --> 00:10:02,067
YOU DON'T HAVE TO GO
TO THE BATHROOM?

76
00:10:02,067 --> 00:10:03,000
NO.

77
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:04,434
YOU DON'T NEED
A DRINK OF WATER?

78
00:10:04,434 --> 00:10:05,400
NO.

79
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:06,934
O.K. GOOD NIGHT,
SWEETHEART.

80
00:10:06,934 --> 00:10:08,234
MMM.

81
00:10:14,300 --> 00:10:16,667
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

82
00:10:16,667 --> 00:10:19,167
NOTHING.

83
00:10:19,167 --> 00:10:22,634
DID YOU HAVE ANOTHER ONE
OF THOSE BAD DREAMS?

84
00:10:23,701 --> 00:10:24,801
ABOUT DADDY?

85
00:10:24,801 --> 00:10:28,834
HIM AND HIS NEW GIRLFRIEND,
THEY WERE BOTH DEAD.

86
00:10:28,834 --> 00:10:30,534
OH...

87
00:10:30,534 --> 00:10:32,601
OH, SWEETHEART,
DADDY'S FINE.

88
00:10:32,601 --> 00:10:35,200
DO YOU WANT TO CALL HIM
JUST TO BE SURE?

89
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:39,234
I'LL BET HE'S STILL UP. IT'S
NOT THAT LATE IN LOS ANGELES.

90
00:10:39,234 --> 00:10:41,501
NO, THANKS.

91
00:10:41,501 --> 00:10:42,501
ALL RIGHT.

92
00:10:42,501 --> 00:10:43,934
WELL, MAYBE LATER.

93
00:10:43,934 --> 00:10:46,167
HEY, MAYBE WE CAN INVITE
HIM TO YOUR BIRTHDAY PARTY.

94
00:10:46,167 --> 00:10:49,334
I THINK I WANT TO GO
TO SLEEP NOW, O.K.?

95
00:10:52,901 --> 00:10:54,267
[SIGHS]

96
00:10:55,434 --> 00:10:57,534
[SEVERAL TELEPHONES RINGING]

97
00:11:29,133 --> 00:11:33,601
WELL, I SEE YOU FOUND
YOUR FRIEND, ALL RIGHT.

98
00:11:33,601 --> 00:11:34,968
ANOTHER ONE OF YOUR JOKES?

99
00:11:34,968 --> 00:11:37,033
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

100
00:11:37,033 --> 00:11:39,334
YOU ASKED
FOR THIS STUFF.

101
00:11:39,334 --> 00:11:40,300
WHAT?

102
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:42,701
PRISON IMPOUNDS
DROPPED IT OFF.

103
00:11:42,701 --> 00:11:46,067
THEY HAD AN EVIDENCE REQUISITION
REQUEST WITH YOUR SIGNATURE.

104
00:11:46,067 --> 00:11:47,067
OH, CHRIST.

105
00:11:47,067 --> 00:11:50,167
I COMPLETELY FORGOT.

106
00:11:50,167 --> 00:11:53,000
I ASKED FOR THIS STUFF
THREE MONTHS AGO.

107
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:54,834
THOUGHT IT MIGHT HELP
WITH THE APPEAL.

108
00:11:54,834 --> 00:11:55,801
OH, WELL.

109
00:11:55,801 --> 00:11:57,934
BETTER LATE
THAN NEVER.

110
00:11:59,634 --> 00:12:01,367
WHEN'S THE DECISION?

111
00:12:01,367 --> 00:12:02,300
TOMORROW.

112
00:12:02,300 --> 00:12:04,734
AND IF THE JUDGE SAYS NO,

113
00:12:04,734 --> 00:12:07,534
I'M ALL SET
TO ASK THE GOVERNOR

114
00:12:07,534 --> 00:12:09,734
FOR A STAY OF EXECUTION.

115
00:12:09,734 --> 00:12:12,667
NEVER HAPPEN.

116
00:12:12,667 --> 00:12:14,934
NOT IN AN ELECTION YEAR.

117
00:12:26,467 --> 00:12:28,934
"AND WHEN SHE REACHED
THE EDGE OF THE CLIFF,

118
00:12:28,934 --> 00:12:31,534
"MATILDA LOOKED DOWN
AT THE BIG GREEN OCEAN.

119
00:12:31,534 --> 00:12:34,501
"AND THEN SHE PULLED THE HAND
MIRROR OUT OF HER BACKPACK

120
00:12:34,501 --> 00:12:36,767
"AND STARED
INTO ITS SHINY SURFACE.

121
00:12:36,767 --> 00:12:39,901
"MATILDA'S REFLECTION
WAS STILL BEAUTIFUL,

122
00:12:39,901 --> 00:12:43,834
"AND THE MIRROR'S FRAME AND
HANDLE WERE STILL MADE OF GOLD,

123
00:12:43,834 --> 00:12:46,000
"ENCRUSTED WITH JEWELS.

124
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:49,167
"BUT MATILDA WAS NO LONGER
BLINDED BY THE BEAUTY.

125
00:12:49,167 --> 00:12:54,367
"SHE DROPPED THE MIRROR INTO
THE OCEAN AND RAN HOME, HAPPY--

126
00:12:54,367 --> 00:12:56,868
HAPPY TO BE
JUST PLAIN MATILDA."

127
00:12:56,868 --> 00:12:58,118
SO...

128
00:12:59,667 --> 00:13:02,267
WHO CAN TELL ME THE MORAL?

129
00:13:02,267 --> 00:13:03,267
BETH?

130
00:13:03,267 --> 00:13:05,400
THE MORAL?
[KIDS GIGGLING]

131
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:07,367
YOU WERE LISTENING,
WEREN'T YOU?

132
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:10,300
YEAH, SORT OF.

133
00:13:10,300 --> 00:13:12,567
THAT'S WHAT I THOUGHT.

134
00:13:12,567 --> 00:13:15,367
ZOE, WOULD YOU CARE
TO GIVE BETH A HAND?

135
00:13:17,334 --> 00:13:19,300
I THINK WHAT IT'S SAYING

136
00:13:19,300 --> 00:13:21,300
IS THAT BAD THINGS
DON'T ALWAYS LOOK BAD.

137
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:23,033
SOMETIMES
THEY EVEN LOOK GOOD.

138
00:13:23,033 --> 00:13:25,868
SO YOU THINK THE MIRROR
IS A BAD THING?

139
00:13:25,868 --> 00:13:27,801
WELL,
WHEN MATILDA FINDS IT,

140
00:13:27,801 --> 00:13:31,767
SHE THINKS IT'S GOING TO MAKE
HER BEAUTIFUL AND POPULAR,

141
00:13:31,767 --> 00:13:35,968
BUT ALL IT REALLY DOES IS
MAKE HER STUCK UP AND MEAN.

142
00:13:35,968 --> 00:13:38,901
WHAT DO YOU THINK, BETH?
IS ZOE RIGHT?

143
00:13:38,901 --> 00:13:41,667
UH, UM, YEAH, I GUESS.

144
00:13:41,667 --> 00:13:45,334
WELL, THEN, WHEN THE TWO BEST
STUDENTS IN THE CLASS AGREE,

145
00:13:45,334 --> 00:13:47,200
THEN IT MUST BE RIGHT.

146
00:13:47,200 --> 00:13:50,267
<i>O.K. NEXT WEEK WE'RE
GOING TO START DR. DOLITTLE.</i>

147
00:13:50,267 --> 00:13:52,734
GOOD. BETH LOVES
TO DO LITTLE.

148
00:13:52,734 --> 00:13:55,834
[GIGGLING]

149
00:13:55,834 --> 00:13:56,934
[GIGGLING STOPS]

150
00:13:58,767 --> 00:14:00,734
WELL, IT'S A LONG SHOT,

151
00:14:00,734 --> 00:14:04,100
BUT I FILED AN APPEAL TO HAVE
YOUR SENTENCE COMMUTED TO LIFE.

152
00:14:04,100 --> 00:14:07,133
THE JUDGE IS TAKING A FEW
DAYS TO THINK ABOUT IT,

153
00:14:07,133 --> 00:14:09,100
WHICH IS POSSIBLY
A GOOD SIGN.

154
00:14:09,100 --> 00:14:11,467
AT LEAST SHE DIDN'T
DENY IT RIGHT AWAY.

155
00:14:11,467 --> 00:14:13,868
WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

156
00:14:13,868 --> 00:14:16,434
I'M TALKING ABOUT
SAVING YOUR LIFE.

157
00:14:16,434 --> 00:14:17,434
WHY?

158
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:20,834
WHAT DO YOU MEAN, WHY?

159
00:14:20,834 --> 00:14:22,267
LISTEN TO ME.

160
00:14:24,634 --> 00:14:26,400
I KILLED MY SON.

161
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:32,601
EVEN IF I WERE FREE,
MY LIFE WOULD BE MEANINGLESS.

162
00:14:32,601 --> 00:14:35,267
SO TELL ME...

163
00:14:35,267 --> 00:14:39,400
WHY WOULD I WANT TO EXTEND
IT HERE IN THIS HELLHOLE, HUH?

164
00:14:42,234 --> 00:14:45,501
BUT I KNOW YOU DIDN'T
COMMIT THOSE OTHER MURDERS,

165
00:14:45,501 --> 00:14:49,567
AND THAT MEANS THE REAL
KILLER IS OUT THERE SOMEWHERE.

166
00:14:49,567 --> 00:14:52,167
THERE'S NO ONE OUT THERE.

167
00:14:54,334 --> 00:14:55,868
WHAT?

168
00:14:55,868 --> 00:14:58,834
THE OTHER CHILDREN?

169
00:14:58,834 --> 00:15:00,367
I MURDERED THEM.

170
00:15:02,734 --> 00:15:06,100
THEN WHY HAVE YOU KEPT
SILENT ALL THIS TIME?

171
00:15:06,100 --> 00:15:07,234
HUH?

172
00:15:16,968 --> 00:15:19,067
[GUARD]
OFF THE GLASS, GOTTO!

173
00:15:23,100 --> 00:15:26,300
THAT'S VERY IMPRESSIVE,
BUT I'M NOT CONVINCED.

174
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:29,234
WHY DID YOU BURY HIM
WITH THE PUPPET?

175
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:32,968
PINOCCHIO?

176
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:37,534
IT WAS HIS FAVORITE.

177
00:15:41,167 --> 00:15:44,300
I MADE IT FOR HIM MYSELF.

178
00:15:44,300 --> 00:15:47,634
[GUARD]
OFF THE GLASS!

179
00:15:47,634 --> 00:15:49,467
FOR HIS LAST BIRTHDAY.

180
00:15:55,367 --> 00:16:00,000
THAT'S NOT EXACTLY THE ACTIONS
OF A DERANGED MURDERER.

181
00:16:02,968 --> 00:16:06,567
WHAT WOULD YOU KNOW
ABOUT A DERANGED MURDERER?

182
00:16:06,567 --> 00:16:09,100
WHO ARE YOU PROTECTING?

183
00:16:09,100 --> 00:16:10,434
NO ONE.

184
00:16:12,400 --> 00:16:13,934
IT WAS ME.

185
00:16:17,300 --> 00:16:19,934
JUST LET ME DIE.

186
00:16:19,934 --> 00:16:20,968
HMM?

187
00:16:23,868 --> 00:16:25,968
PLEASE.

188
00:16:25,968 --> 00:16:28,133
WAIT. MR. GOTTO.

189
00:16:30,200 --> 00:16:31,734
[DOOR OPENS]

190
00:16:36,501 --> 00:16:38,267
MR. GOTTO!

191
00:16:38,267 --> 00:16:40,667
WHO REALLY KILLED
THOSE CHILDREN?

192
00:16:40,667 --> 00:16:44,133
SOMEONE CLOSE TO YOU? IS THAT
WHY YOU'RE PROTECTING HIM?

193
00:16:44,133 --> 00:16:46,834
MR. GOTTO!

194
00:16:48,634 --> 00:16:50,501
STAY OUT OF IT!

195
00:16:50,501 --> 00:16:51,968
LET ME DIE!

196
00:16:51,968 --> 00:16:53,701
VISITING ROOM THREE!
ON THE DOUBLE!

197
00:16:53,701 --> 00:16:55,968
JUST LET ME FUCKIN' DIE!

198
00:16:55,968 --> 00:16:57,567
PLEASE...

199
00:16:57,567 --> 00:16:59,067
STAY OUT OF IT!

200
00:16:59,067 --> 00:17:00,534
JUST LET ME DIE!

201
00:17:00,534 --> 00:17:01,567
PLEASE!

202
00:17:03,934 --> 00:17:05,467
[DOOR CLOSES]

203
00:17:08,167 --> 00:17:09,701
[BELL RINGS]

204
00:17:15,100 --> 00:17:18,100
PARTY AT MY HOUSE.
THIS FRIDAY AFTER SCHOOL.

205
00:17:18,100 --> 00:17:19,601
IT'S GOING TO BE GREAT.

206
00:17:22,300 --> 00:17:25,334
THANKS, ZOE-BLOWY.
I NEVER MISS A PARTY.

207
00:17:25,334 --> 00:17:26,300
HA HA HA HA!

208
00:17:26,300 --> 00:17:27,868
COME ON, BETH,
GIVE THEM BACK!

209
00:17:27,868 --> 00:17:29,300
GIVE THEM BACK, BETH!

210
00:17:31,501 --> 00:17:33,367
I MEAN IT!

211
00:17:33,367 --> 00:17:35,234
WHAT? I'M NOT INVITED?

212
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:38,234
WHAT YOU GOING TO DO?

213
00:17:50,200 --> 00:17:51,601
COME ON, BETH!

214
00:17:51,601 --> 00:17:53,434
YOU CAN DO IT!
COME ON!

215
00:17:53,434 --> 00:17:56,400
AAH! GET HER OFF!
GET HER OFF! GET HER OFF!

216
00:17:56,400 --> 00:17:57,968
[PANTING]

217
00:17:57,968 --> 00:17:59,434
OHH...

218
00:18:09,801 --> 00:18:11,934
I TOLD YOU
SHE WAS CRAZY.

219
00:18:11,934 --> 00:18:13,467
YEAH. COME ON.

220
00:18:16,334 --> 00:18:19,067
YOU SHOWED HER, BETH.

221
00:18:53,834 --> 00:18:55,667
HOW WAS SCHOOL TODAY?

222
00:19:03,834 --> 00:19:05,734
NOTHING SPECIAL.

223
00:19:07,100 --> 00:19:10,367
YOUR MOTHER TELLS ME
YOU HAD ANOTHER NIGHTMARE.

224
00:19:14,734 --> 00:19:17,200
DON'T YOU THINK
WE SHOULD TALK ABOUT IT?

225
00:19:17,200 --> 00:19:18,501
NO.

226
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:25,767
WHEN SOMEBODY HURTS US,
SOMEBODY WE'VE TRUSTED,

227
00:19:25,767 --> 00:19:29,601
IT'S NATURAL, EVEN HEALTHY,
TO BE ANGRY WITH THEM.

228
00:19:29,601 --> 00:19:32,968
IT'S PART OF
THE HEALING PROCESS.

229
00:19:32,968 --> 00:19:36,000
BUT IT'S TIME
TO MOVE ON, ZOE.

230
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:38,534
YOU HAVE TO LEARN
TO FORGIVE HIM.

231
00:19:38,534 --> 00:19:41,567
FORGIVE WHO?

232
00:19:44,267 --> 00:19:46,234
WELL, YOU CAN BE SURE IT'S
NOT GOING TO HAPPEN AGAIN.

233
00:19:46,234 --> 00:19:47,234
I HOPE NOT.

234
00:19:47,234 --> 00:19:48,701
NO. I UNDERSTAND.

235
00:19:48,701 --> 00:19:51,434
AGAIN, I'M REALLY SORRY.

236
00:19:51,434 --> 00:19:52,934
ALL RIGHT. BYE.

237
00:19:54,868 --> 00:19:56,567
ZOE.

238
00:19:56,567 --> 00:19:58,467
THAT WAS A MRS. WAYNE.

239
00:19:58,467 --> 00:19:59,968
SHE'S UNDERSTANDABLY UPSET,

240
00:19:59,968 --> 00:20:01,701
CONSIDERING SHE JUST CAME
BACK FROM THE HOSPITAL,

241
00:20:01,701 --> 00:20:03,400
WHERE HER DAUGHTER HAD
TWO STITCHES IN HER EAR.

242
00:20:03,400 --> 00:20:04,634
SHE SAID YOU BIT HER.

243
00:20:04,634 --> 00:20:06,601
SHE STARTED IT.

244
00:20:06,601 --> 00:20:08,834
I DON'T CARE
WHO STARTED IT.

245
00:20:08,834 --> 00:20:11,834
WE DON'T BITE PEOPLE
IN THIS HOUSE.

246
00:20:11,834 --> 00:20:14,701
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

247
00:20:16,901 --> 00:20:17,868
HELLO.

248
00:20:17,868 --> 00:20:20,167
OH, HI, WARREN.
GOOD TIMING.

249
00:20:20,167 --> 00:20:21,200
REALLY?

250
00:20:21,200 --> 00:20:23,267
YEAH. ZOE HAD ANOTHER
FIGHT AT SCHOOL TODAY.

251
00:20:23,267 --> 00:20:26,534
WHAT? SHE CAN'T AFFORD
TO GET THROWN OUT AGAIN.

252
00:20:26,534 --> 00:20:27,934
I KNOW THAT.

253
00:20:27,934 --> 00:20:31,601
I--I CAN'T EXACTLY FOLLOW
HER TO CLASSES ALL DAY.

254
00:20:31,601 --> 00:20:34,100
HERE. YOU TALK TO HER.

255
00:20:34,100 --> 00:20:36,634
ZOE, IT'S DADDY.

256
00:20:36,634 --> 00:20:38,467
[WARREN]
HELLO, ZOE.

257
00:20:38,467 --> 00:20:39,467
ZOE?

258
00:20:39,467 --> 00:20:40,834
HELLO?

259
00:20:40,834 --> 00:20:42,434
HELLO?

260
00:20:42,434 --> 00:20:43,400
ZOE?

261
00:20:43,400 --> 00:20:45,400
WARREN, I'LL CALL YOU LATER.

262
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:46,901
O.K.
BYE.

263
00:20:46,901 --> 00:20:49,033
YOU'RE GROUNDED,
YOUNG LADY.

264
00:20:49,033 --> 00:20:53,100
NO TV AND NO PLAYING
AFTER SCHOOL FOR TWO WEEKS!

265
00:21:04,634 --> 00:21:05,801
[DOOR SLAMS]

266
00:21:07,534 --> 00:21:08,968
MMM...

267
00:21:08,968 --> 00:21:12,367
YOU KNOW, HER BIRTHDAY
IS THIS FRIDAY.

268
00:21:13,334 --> 00:21:15,901
OH, SHIT.

269
00:21:15,901 --> 00:21:18,200
WELL, SHE'S GROUNDED
TILL THEN.

270
00:21:24,734 --> 00:21:26,033
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

271
00:21:29,200 --> 00:21:30,734
MAY I COME IN?

272
00:21:32,434 --> 00:21:34,567
CAN I GET YOU ANYTHING?

273
00:21:38,501 --> 00:21:42,200
HOW ABOUT MRS. PIGGLE WIG,
HMM?

274
00:21:44,067 --> 00:21:47,767
NAH. SHE'S MAD AT ME. I
FORGOT TO BRUSH OUT HER TAIL.

275
00:21:49,567 --> 00:21:50,767
BUT...

276
00:21:50,767 --> 00:21:54,367
WALTER SAYS HE WANTS
TO SLEEP WITH ME TONIGHT.

277
00:21:56,167 --> 00:21:57,634
WHAT ELSE IS NEW?

278
00:21:57,634 --> 00:22:00,434
WALTER ALWAYS WANTS
TO SLEEP WITH YOU.

279
00:22:07,501 --> 00:22:10,634
WHY DOES SHE ALWAYS TAKE
EVERYONE ELSE'S SIDE?

280
00:22:11,667 --> 00:22:13,467
SHE DOESN'T, HONEY.

281
00:22:15,734 --> 00:22:18,267
SHE'S UNDER A LOT
OF STRESS RIGHT NOW,

282
00:22:18,267 --> 00:22:20,634
SO WE HAVE TO TRY
AND HELP HER OUT

283
00:22:20,634 --> 00:22:22,400
AS MUCH
AS WE POSSIBLY CAN.

284
00:22:22,400 --> 00:22:23,868
I DO TRY, REALLY.

285
00:22:23,868 --> 00:22:27,267
BUT EVERYTHING ALWAYS
TURNS OUT ALL WRONG.

286
00:22:31,334 --> 00:22:34,367
YOUR ARGUMENT HAS BEEN
WELL-THOUGHT-OUT AND PRESENTED,

287
00:22:34,367 --> 00:22:37,567
AND I HAVE GIVEN IT A GREAT
DEAL OF CONSIDERATION.

288
00:22:37,567 --> 00:22:39,834
AND ALTHOUGH I BELIEVE
YOU MAY HAVE A VALID POINT

289
00:22:39,834 --> 00:22:43,267
ABOUT THE CIRCUMSTANCES SURROUNDING
YOUR CLIENT'S SENTENCING,

290
00:22:43,267 --> 00:22:45,634
THE FACT REMAINS THAT
IN THE EYES OF THE LAW,

291
00:22:45,634 --> 00:22:49,701
A ONE-TIME MURDERER IS JUST AS
GUILTY AS A MULTIPLE MURDERER.

292
00:22:49,701 --> 00:22:51,667
THEREFORE, I CAN FIND
NO JUSTIFICATION

293
00:22:51,667 --> 00:22:54,868
IN OVERTURNING JUDGE OLSON'S
ORIGINAL SENTENCE.

294
00:22:54,868 --> 00:22:56,100
MOTION DENIED.

295
00:22:57,367 --> 00:23:02,000
JENNIFER! IS THIS
YOUR LAST HOPE?

296
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:05,200
WILL YOU APPEAL
THE COURT'S DECISION?

297
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:07,734
VINCENT GOTTO IS A VICTIM
OF PUBLIC OPINION

298
00:23:07,734 --> 00:23:09,234
AND MEDIA HYPE.

299
00:23:09,234 --> 00:23:10,400
A BROADCAST THE OTHER NIGHT

300
00:23:10,400 --> 00:23:12,033
REFERRED TO HIM AS
A CONVICTED SERIAL KILLER,

301
00:23:12,033 --> 00:23:13,868
WHEN IN FACT HE'S NOT.

302
00:23:13,868 --> 00:23:15,334
EXCUSE ME, PLEASE.

303
00:23:15,334 --> 00:23:18,067
WILL YOU BE A WITNESS
AT THE EXECUTION?

304
00:23:19,868 --> 00:23:21,467
[DOOR CLANGS]

305
00:23:21,467 --> 00:23:23,634
[PRIEST]
THE LORD IS MY SHEPHERD.

306
00:23:23,634 --> 00:23:26,300
I SHALL NOT WANT.

307
00:23:26,300 --> 00:23:29,634
HE MAKETH ME TO LIE DOWN
IN GREEN PASTURES.

308
00:23:29,634 --> 00:23:32,400
HE LEADETH ME
BESIDE THE STILL WATERS.

309
00:23:32,400 --> 00:23:35,767
HE RESTORETH MY SOUL.

310
00:23:35,767 --> 00:23:38,400
HE LEADETH ME IN THE PATHS
OF RIGHTEOUSNESS

311
00:23:38,400 --> 00:23:39,634
FOR HIS NAME'S SAKE.

312
00:23:39,634 --> 00:23:42,667
THOU ANOINTEST
MY HEAD WITH OIL.

313
00:23:42,667 --> 00:23:44,734
MY CUP RUNNETH OVER.

314
00:23:46,300 --> 00:23:47,767
SURELY GOODNESS AND MERCY

315
00:23:47,767 --> 00:23:51,100
SHALL FOLLOW ME
ALL THE DAYS OF MY LIFE,

316
00:23:51,100 --> 00:23:54,234
AND I WILL DWELL
IN THE HOUSE OF THE LORD

317
00:23:54,234 --> 00:23:55,968
FOREVER.

318
00:25:10,100 --> 00:25:11,734
[BELL RINGS]

319
00:25:17,467 --> 00:25:18,701
ARRRGH!

320
00:25:25,133 --> 00:25:26,734
ARRRGH!

321
00:25:35,033 --> 00:25:36,934
[GASPS]

322
00:26:13,968 --> 00:26:15,601
CAN I HELP YOU?
[GASPS]

323
00:26:15,601 --> 00:26:19,734
I'M SOR--I'M SORRY. I--I
DIDN'T MEAN TO STARTLE YOU.

324
00:26:19,734 --> 00:26:21,234
NO. IT'S O.K.

325
00:26:21,234 --> 00:26:23,267
ARE YOU A MEMBER
OF THIS PARISH?

326
00:26:23,267 --> 00:26:24,107
NO, NO.

327
00:26:25,601 --> 00:26:27,033
ACTUALLY,
TECHNICALLY SPEAKING,

328
00:26:27,033 --> 00:26:29,567
I'M NOT EVEN
A CATHOLIC ANYMORE.

329
00:26:29,567 --> 00:26:32,267
I WAS DIVORCED
LAST YEAR.

330
00:26:32,267 --> 00:26:33,234
THAT'S O.K.

331
00:26:33,234 --> 00:26:35,534
THIS ISN'T
A CATHOLIC CHURCH.

332
00:26:35,534 --> 00:26:38,133
IT'S EPISCOPALIAN.

333
00:26:38,133 --> 00:26:42,133
IT'S, UH, SORT OF LIKE
CATHOLIC LIGHT.

334
00:26:43,934 --> 00:26:45,601
HA HA HA HA!

335
00:26:45,601 --> 00:26:48,133
COULD I, UM...

336
00:26:48,133 --> 00:26:51,000
UH, BUY YOU
A CUP OF COFFEE?

337
00:26:54,834 --> 00:26:57,801
SO I QUIT THE FIRM,
AND I TOOK A POSITION

338
00:26:57,801 --> 00:26:59,567
AT THE PUBLIC
DEFENDER'S OFFICE.

339
00:26:59,567 --> 00:27:01,567
IT'S A LOT LESS MONEY,

340
00:27:01,567 --> 00:27:05,133
BUT THE SHORTER HOURS ALLOW
ME MORE TIME WITH ZOE.

341
00:27:05,133 --> 00:27:08,200
SEEMS AS THOUGH YOU'VE
MANAGED TO MAKE THE BEST

342
00:27:08,200 --> 00:27:10,334
OF A DIFFICULT SITUATION.

343
00:27:12,267 --> 00:27:14,067
I WONDER.

344
00:27:14,067 --> 00:27:16,033
WHY IS THAT?

345
00:27:16,033 --> 00:27:19,434
ZOE'S BEEN
HAVING THESE...

346
00:27:19,434 --> 00:27:22,033
HORRIBLE, VIOLENT
NIGHTMARES LATELY,

347
00:27:22,033 --> 00:27:24,167
EVER SINCE
I BECAME A P.D.

348
00:27:24,167 --> 00:27:28,968
HER THERAPIST THINKS SHE HAS
A LOT OF REPRESSED HOSTILITY.

349
00:27:28,968 --> 00:27:30,501
OH, I...

350
00:27:30,501 --> 00:27:34,734
YOU THINK YOUR JOB
IS TAKING ITS TOLL ON HER.

351
00:27:34,734 --> 00:27:36,667
NOT JUST ON HER.

352
00:27:40,033 --> 00:27:43,434
YOU KNOW, I DEAL WITH A LOT
OF BAD PEOPLE IN MY JOB.

353
00:27:43,434 --> 00:27:46,501
I PUT A LOT OF THEM
ON THE STREET.

354
00:27:47,767 --> 00:27:50,400
AND THE FIRST TIME
I HAD A CLIENT

355
00:27:50,400 --> 00:27:52,968
THAT I THOUGHT
WAS ACTUALLY INNOCENT,

356
00:27:52,968 --> 00:27:54,534
I COULDN'T SAVE HIM.

357
00:28:01,868 --> 00:28:03,534
[DOOR CLOSES]

358
00:28:12,300 --> 00:28:15,000
YOU DID EVERYTHING
YOU COULD, JENNY.

359
00:28:15,000 --> 00:28:16,601
LET IT GO...

360
00:28:16,601 --> 00:28:18,834
OR IT'LL
TEAR YOU UP INSIDE.

361
00:28:18,834 --> 00:28:21,467
HOW COULD THE MAN
WHO MADE THIS

362
00:28:21,467 --> 00:28:23,801
HAVE MURDERED
HIS ONLY CHILD?

363
00:28:23,801 --> 00:28:27,734
EVIL COMES IN ALL
SHAPES AND SIZES.

364
00:28:27,734 --> 00:28:30,534
MAYBE HE DID KILL
ALL THE OTHERS.

365
00:28:30,534 --> 00:28:31,767
NO.

366
00:28:31,767 --> 00:28:34,901
ALL THE OTHER CHILDREN WERE
BEATEN WITH A BLUNT OBJECT.

367
00:28:34,901 --> 00:28:36,234
HIS SON WAS STRANGLED.

368
00:28:36,234 --> 00:28:36,984
SO?

369
00:28:37,701 --> 00:28:39,868
SO WHY
THE DIFFERENT M.O.?

370
00:28:39,868 --> 00:28:43,133
MAYBE...THE OTHER
MURDERS WERE PLANNED,

371
00:28:43,133 --> 00:28:45,701
BUT HIS SON WAS
SPUR OF THE MOMENT.

372
00:28:45,701 --> 00:28:47,100
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

373
00:28:47,100 --> 00:28:50,067
MAYBE HIS SON FOUND
OUT WHAT HE WAS DOING,

374
00:28:50,067 --> 00:28:51,901
AND HE HAD TO
GET RID OF HIM...

375
00:28:51,901 --> 00:28:52,934
FAST.

376
00:28:54,501 --> 00:28:55,251
NO.

377
00:28:55,968 --> 00:28:59,400
GOTTO WAS DEFINITELY
PROTECTING SOMEONE.

378
00:28:59,400 --> 00:29:02,767
BUT THE KILLINGS STOPPED
AFTER HE WAS ARRESTED, RIGHT?

379
00:29:04,934 --> 00:29:08,100
SO HOW DO YOU
EXPLAIN THAT?

380
00:29:17,734 --> 00:29:19,300
HAVE A GOOD WEEKEND,
JENNIFER.

381
00:29:19,300 --> 00:29:20,801
GOOD NIGHT.
YOU, TOO.

382
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:32,750
OW!

383
00:29:33,567 --> 00:29:36,133
OH, DAMN,
ANOTHER NAIL GONE.

384
00:29:42,734 --> 00:29:44,667
[SPEED DIAL BEEPING]

385
00:29:44,667 --> 00:29:46,968
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

386
00:29:49,267 --> 00:29:50,701
GARRICK RESIDENCE.

387
00:29:50,701 --> 00:29:52,200
SOPHIA, HI. IT'S ME.

388
00:29:52,200 --> 00:29:54,300
HEY, DID WARREN
REMEMBER TO CALL ZOE?

389
00:29:54,300 --> 00:29:58,033
YEAH, BUT, UH, SHE
WOULDN'T COME TO THE PHONE.

390
00:29:58,033 --> 00:30:00,534
OH, MAN,
SHE'S RELENTLESS.

391
00:30:00,534 --> 00:30:03,200
WONDER WHERE
SHE GETS IT FROM.

392
00:30:03,200 --> 00:30:05,734
LISTEN, UM,
THE TOY STORE CALLED,

393
00:30:05,734 --> 00:30:07,868
SAID THERE WAS
A MIX-UP IN SHIPPING

394
00:30:07,868 --> 00:30:09,434
AND THEY WON'T HAVE
THE DOLL TILL MONDAY.

395
00:30:09,434 --> 00:30:10,467
YOU'RE KIDDING.

396
00:30:10,467 --> 00:30:12,767
DID YOU TELL THEM
I HAD TO HAVE IT TODAY?

397
00:30:12,767 --> 00:30:13,734
OF COURSE.

398
00:30:13,734 --> 00:30:15,534
THEY SAID
THEY WERE VERY SORRY,

399
00:30:15,534 --> 00:30:18,067
BUT THERE'S NOTHING
THAT THEY COULD DO.

400
00:30:18,067 --> 00:30:21,334
OH, GREAT. O.K., UM...

401
00:30:21,334 --> 00:30:24,567
WELL, I GUESS I'LL LOOK
FOR IT SOMEWHERE ELSE

402
00:30:24,567 --> 00:30:26,400
WHEN I GO GET THE PIZZA
AND THE CAKE.

403
00:30:26,400 --> 00:30:27,701
I DON'T KNOW.

404
00:30:27,701 --> 00:30:29,300
BYE.

405
00:31:03,067 --> 00:31:04,601
HI, YOU GUYS.

406
00:31:04,601 --> 00:31:05,534
HEY, MOM.

407
00:31:05,534 --> 00:31:07,267
SWEETHEART,
SORRY I'M LATE.

408
00:31:07,267 --> 00:31:08,968
CAN I GET UNDER HERE?

409
00:31:08,968 --> 00:31:10,567
WHAT'S IN THERE?

410
00:31:10,567 --> 00:31:11,901
DON'T ASK.

411
00:31:15,033 --> 00:31:17,534
HEY, I WAS JUST ABOUT TO SEND
OUT A SEARCH PARTY FOR YOU.

412
00:31:17,534 --> 00:31:19,534
OH, THE CAKE WASN'T DONE
WHEN I GOT THERE,

413
00:31:19,534 --> 00:31:22,033
AND I HAD TO GO ALL OVER
TOWN TO GET THAT DAMN DOLL.

414
00:31:22,033 --> 00:31:24,100
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT. WHOA,
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

415
00:31:24,100 --> 00:31:25,534
JUST--TIME-OUT. RELAX.

416
00:31:25,534 --> 00:31:27,567
DAVID, I CAN'T. THE KIDS ARE
GOING TO BE HERE ANY MINUTE.

417
00:31:27,567 --> 00:31:29,033
SOPHIA AND I
CAN HANDLE IT.

418
00:31:29,033 --> 00:31:31,801
I GOT A TRUNKFUL
OF STUFF IN THE CAR...

419
00:31:31,801 --> 00:31:33,267
I CAN GET IT.

420
00:31:33,267 --> 00:31:34,434
I WILL GET IT.

421
00:31:34,434 --> 00:31:37,000
WHY DON'T YOU GO AND
CHANGE CLOTHES AND RELAX,

422
00:31:37,000 --> 00:31:39,367
AND I'LL CALL YOU WHEN
EVERYBODY GETS HERE?

423
00:31:39,367 --> 00:31:41,434
THE DECORATIONS AREN'T--
I JUST WANT--

424
00:31:41,434 --> 00:31:42,434
DAVID.

425
00:31:42,434 --> 00:31:43,868
NO, NO, NO.

426
00:31:43,868 --> 00:31:45,100
DAVID, COME ON.
YOU CAN'T.

427
00:31:45,100 --> 00:31:46,100
BUT YOU--

428
00:31:46,100 --> 00:31:47,067
NO BUTS.

429
00:31:47,067 --> 00:31:49,133
GO ON.
TAKE A HIKE.

430
00:31:52,067 --> 00:31:53,634
DON'T MESS UP.

431
00:31:55,133 --> 00:31:56,601
THANKS. I OWE YOU.

432
00:31:56,601 --> 00:31:58,200
THAT'S TRUE...

433
00:31:58,200 --> 00:32:00,701
AND I'M GOING TO
COLLECT LATER.

434
00:32:00,701 --> 00:32:02,200
[CHILDREN CHEERING]

435
00:32:14,667 --> 00:32:17,167
[DAVID] READY? ONE MORE
TIME. ONE MORE TIME.

436
00:32:17,167 --> 00:32:18,167
OHH!

437
00:32:20,634 --> 00:32:22,734
O.K., WHO'S
GOING TO GET CANDY?

438
00:32:22,734 --> 00:32:24,734
I AM!
I AM!

439
00:32:24,734 --> 00:32:26,501
WHO'S GOING TO GET CANDY?

440
00:32:26,501 --> 00:32:28,334
ME, ME, ME, ME!

441
00:32:30,000 --> 00:32:31,033
HEY!

442
00:32:33,167 --> 00:32:34,634
OH, MOMMY, IT'S GREAT.

443
00:32:34,634 --> 00:32:36,367
IT'S EVEN BETTER
THAN I HOPED.

444
00:32:36,367 --> 00:32:37,334
IT IS? OH, GOOD.

445
00:32:37,334 --> 00:32:40,100
[CHILD]
ME, ME, ME, ME!

446
00:32:44,133 --> 00:32:46,234
I'M SORRY.

447
00:32:46,234 --> 00:32:48,100
SHE SPOTTED IT BEFORE
I COULD GET IT WRAPPED.

448
00:32:48,100 --> 00:32:49,400
WHERE'D YOU FIND
THAT THING?

449
00:32:49,400 --> 00:32:50,534
IT LOOKS HAND-CARVED.

450
00:33:08,701 --> 00:33:11,801
[SINGING
AND OVERLAPPING VOICES]

451
00:33:31,534 --> 00:33:32,701
I'LL TALK TO YOU SOON.

452
00:33:32,701 --> 00:33:33,767
COME ON, SWEETIE.

453
00:33:33,767 --> 00:33:34,834
O.K., MOMMY.

454
00:33:34,834 --> 00:33:36,567
BYE. SEE YOU
AT SCHOOL.

455
00:33:36,567 --> 00:33:37,567
O.K.

456
00:33:37,567 --> 00:33:38,868
BYE, YOU GUYS.

457
00:33:38,868 --> 00:33:40,267
BYE!

458
00:33:41,300 --> 00:33:43,000
YAHOO!

459
00:33:47,200 --> 00:33:49,334
HAS ANYONE SEEN
PINOCCHIO?

460
00:33:49,334 --> 00:33:50,334
HE'S MISSING?

461
00:33:50,334 --> 00:33:52,033
HE WAS RIGHT HERE
A MINUTE AGO.

462
00:33:52,033 --> 00:33:54,334
LET'S HAVE A LOOK.

463
00:33:54,334 --> 00:33:55,634
[HIGH-PITCHED VOICE]
HERE I AM.

464
00:33:58,767 --> 00:34:02,133
JUST WANTED TO MAKE SURE
THE FIRE WAS OUT.

465
00:34:03,567 --> 00:34:05,100
WOOD, YOU KNOW?

466
00:34:06,267 --> 00:34:09,067
[EVERYONE LAUGHING]

467
00:34:12,534 --> 00:34:15,767
HA HA HA HA!

468
00:34:15,767 --> 00:34:16,801
HELP!

469
00:34:18,100 --> 00:34:20,534
ZOE, YOU'LL HAVE TO
FORGIVE DAVID.

470
00:34:20,534 --> 00:34:21,667
WOOD, YOU KNOW.

471
00:34:21,667 --> 00:34:23,067
HA HA HA...

472
00:34:28,534 --> 00:34:29,934
SOPHIA,

473
00:34:29,934 --> 00:34:31,901
WHY DON'T YOU LEAVE THOSE?
I'LL DO THOSE TOMORROW.

474
00:34:31,901 --> 00:34:33,968
OH, I DON'T MIND.

475
00:34:33,968 --> 00:34:36,000
COME ON, IT'S LATE. I'LL
DO THEM IN THE MORNING.

476
00:34:36,000 --> 00:34:37,434
YOU SURE?

477
00:34:37,434 --> 00:34:39,367
YEAH.
YOU'VE DONE ENOUGH.

478
00:34:39,367 --> 00:34:41,300
ALL RIGHT, THEN.

479
00:34:41,300 --> 00:34:42,701
I'LL SEE YOU
TOMORROW.

480
00:34:42,701 --> 00:34:44,234
O.K. GOOD NIGHT.

481
00:34:54,734 --> 00:34:55,968
HEY, YOU.

482
00:34:57,501 --> 00:34:59,033
HEY, YOU.

483
00:34:59,033 --> 00:35:00,934
HOW YOU DOING?

484
00:35:00,934 --> 00:35:02,033
O.K.

485
00:35:41,300 --> 00:35:42,334
[GASP]

486
00:35:44,601 --> 00:35:47,767
OH, HO HO HO HO.

487
00:35:47,767 --> 00:35:48,767
HO HO.

488
00:35:48,767 --> 00:35:50,400
GOOD ONE, KIDDO.

489
00:35:50,400 --> 00:35:53,601
ZOE, YOU SCARED THE LIVING
DAYLIGHTS OUT OF ME.

490
00:35:53,601 --> 00:35:55,834
COME ON, MOMMY. IT'S
JUST A LITTLE PUPPET.

491
00:35:55,834 --> 00:35:58,400
OH, NO, NO. IT'S
NOT JUST ANY PUPPET.

492
00:35:58,400 --> 00:36:00,267
THIS IS
PINOCCHIO.

493
00:36:00,267 --> 00:36:02,567
PINOCCHIO
WASN'T SCARY.

494
00:36:02,567 --> 00:36:03,901
HE WAS GOOD.

495
00:36:03,901 --> 00:36:06,100
OH, YOU
THINK SO, HUH?

496
00:36:06,100 --> 00:36:07,901
WASN'T HE?

497
00:36:11,133 --> 00:36:12,667
YEAH,

498
00:36:12,667 --> 00:36:16,701
THAT'S THE ONLY WAY HE COULD
BECOME A REAL LIVE BOY.

499
00:36:16,701 --> 00:36:18,701
HE HAD TO BE GOOD.

500
00:36:18,701 --> 00:36:20,467
WELL, THAT'S TRUE,

501
00:36:20,467 --> 00:36:22,033
AND HE TRIED
TO BE GOOD.

502
00:36:22,033 --> 00:36:24,000
HE TRIED
REALLY HARD,

503
00:36:24,000 --> 00:36:26,634
BUT HE KEPT GIVING
IN TO TEMPTATION

504
00:36:26,634 --> 00:36:30,934
AND DOING THESE
REALLY BAD, BAD THINGS.

505
00:36:30,934 --> 00:36:32,701
AND THAT'S WHY
THE BLUE FAIRY

506
00:36:32,701 --> 00:36:34,234
MADE HIS NOSE
GROW LONGER

507
00:36:34,234 --> 00:36:35,767
EVERY TIME
HE TOLD A LIE.

508
00:36:35,767 --> 00:36:38,634
THAT'S WHY SHE
GAVE HIM A CRICKET

509
00:36:38,634 --> 00:36:40,634
TO ACT
AS HIS CONSCIENCE,

510
00:36:40,634 --> 00:36:42,200
TO TRY TO
KEEP HIM FROM DOING

511
00:36:42,200 --> 00:36:45,634
THESE REALLY
BAD, BAD THINGS.

512
00:36:45,634 --> 00:36:48,534
BUT NOTHING
EVER WORKED.

513
00:36:50,667 --> 00:36:52,868
AND NOW...

514
00:36:52,868 --> 00:36:54,567
<i>HE'S COMING
AFTER YOU!</i>

515
00:36:54,567 --> 00:36:56,634
[SCREAMING]

516
00:37:03,367 --> 00:37:05,467
SO DID YOU HAVE
A GOOD TIME TONIGHT?

517
00:37:05,467 --> 00:37:06,868
YEAH.

518
00:37:06,868 --> 00:37:08,067
GOOD.

519
00:37:08,067 --> 00:37:11,567
HEY, SOPHIA SAID DADDY
CALLED TO SAY HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

520
00:37:13,467 --> 00:37:15,868
SWEETHEART, DADDY
LOVES YOU VERY MUCH.

521
00:37:15,868 --> 00:37:17,067
HE WAS JUST UPSET.

522
00:37:17,067 --> 00:37:20,801
IT'S THE FIRST BIRTHDAY
HE'S EVER MISSED.

523
00:37:20,801 --> 00:37:24,334
PINOCCHIO SAYS HE WANTS
TO SLEEP WITH ME TONIGHT.

524
00:37:24,334 --> 00:37:27,434
PINOCCHIO'S FINE
WHERE HE IS.

525
00:37:27,434 --> 00:37:29,334
NOW, REMEMBER,
PINOCCHIO'S JUST VISITING

526
00:37:29,334 --> 00:37:31,434
UNTIL YOU GET YOUR
REAL PRESENT, O.K.?

527
00:37:33,200 --> 00:37:37,701
BESIDES, HE WOULDN'T WANT
TO SLEEP NEXT TO WALTER.

528
00:37:37,701 --> 00:37:38,767
WHY NOT?

529
00:37:38,767 --> 00:37:40,868
BECAUSE HE GOT SWALLOWED
BY A WHALE, REMEMBER?

530
00:37:40,868 --> 00:37:42,634
ARRRGH!

531
00:37:43,567 --> 00:37:45,868
O.K. GOOD NIGHT,
MOMMY.

532
00:37:45,868 --> 00:37:47,100
OH, I LOVE YOU.

533
00:37:47,100 --> 00:37:48,534
HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

534
00:37:48,534 --> 00:37:49,567
GOOD NIGHT.

535
00:38:16,367 --> 00:38:18,067
SO WHERE WERE WE?

536
00:38:47,133 --> 00:38:48,133
OHH...

537
00:38:48,133 --> 00:38:49,200
MMM...

538
00:38:56,000 --> 00:38:57,601
MMM...

539
00:38:59,400 --> 00:39:01,234
OHH...

540
00:39:06,033 --> 00:39:07,567
AHH...

541
00:39:26,534 --> 00:39:27,901
[THUNK]

542
00:39:39,901 --> 00:39:41,868
THERE YOU GO.

543
00:39:43,400 --> 00:39:45,767
I WISH YOU
WERE A REAL BOY.

544
00:39:45,767 --> 00:39:48,400
THEN I WOULDN'T
BE ALL ALONE.

545
00:40:00,467 --> 00:40:01,567
[ENGINE STARTS]

546
00:41:13,567 --> 00:41:15,000
[GASP]

547
00:41:51,200 --> 00:41:53,300
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
WITH MY PINOCCHIO?

548
00:41:53,300 --> 00:41:55,567
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
IN MY ROOM?

549
00:42:03,534 --> 00:42:06,367
AND THEN DAVID MADE
PINOCCHIO TAP HIS OWN HEAD.

550
00:42:06,367 --> 00:42:09,834
AT FIRST I THOUGHT
IT WAS KIND OF FUNNY,

551
00:42:09,834 --> 00:42:13,467
BUT NOW I THINK HE MIGHT HAVE
HURT PINOCCHIO'S FEELINGS.

552
00:42:13,467 --> 00:42:15,467
SOUNDS LIKE
A GREAT PARTY.

553
00:42:15,467 --> 00:42:17,334
YEAH.

554
00:42:17,334 --> 00:42:19,934
AND IT SOUNDS LIKE YOU AND
YOUR MOM REALLY LIKE DAVID.

555
00:42:19,934 --> 00:42:21,184
YEAH.

556
00:42:22,534 --> 00:42:25,434
YOU DO LIKE DAVID,
DON'T YOU?

557
00:42:25,434 --> 00:42:28,334
YEAH, HE'S O.K.,
BUT...

558
00:42:28,334 --> 00:42:30,067
BUT WHAT?

559
00:42:30,067 --> 00:42:32,200
IF HE TAKES
MY MOM AWAY,

560
00:42:32,200 --> 00:42:34,300
THEN I WON'T
HAVE ANYBODY.

561
00:42:40,634 --> 00:42:41,701
HEY, MOM.

562
00:42:41,701 --> 00:42:43,601
HI, SWEETHEART.

563
00:42:47,200 --> 00:42:48,934
HOW WAS SCHOOL?

564
00:42:48,934 --> 00:42:50,300
O.K.

565
00:42:50,300 --> 00:42:52,434
CAN WE TALK?

566
00:42:52,434 --> 00:42:54,200
WHAT'S UP?

567
00:42:54,200 --> 00:42:55,467
WELL...

568
00:42:55,467 --> 00:42:58,934
SOPHIA SAID THAT YOU SNEAKED
INTO HER ROOM THIS MORNING.

569
00:42:58,934 --> 00:42:59,968
NOT ME.

570
00:42:59,968 --> 00:43:01,634
PINOCCHIO.

571
00:43:01,634 --> 00:43:03,968
HE WAS CURIOUS
ABOUT LADIES' BODIES.

572
00:43:03,968 --> 00:43:06,100
AH, HE WAS, WAS HE?

573
00:43:06,100 --> 00:43:07,033
YEAH.

574
00:43:07,033 --> 00:43:09,000
I TRIED TO
EXPLAIN IT TO HIM,

575
00:43:09,000 --> 00:43:12,601
AFTER HE HEARD YOU AND
DAVID IN YOUR ROOM.

576
00:43:17,467 --> 00:43:19,467
DO YOU WANT TO
TALK ABOUT IT?

577
00:43:19,467 --> 00:43:20,434
NO.

578
00:43:20,434 --> 00:43:21,767
WHAT'S IN THE BAG?

579
00:43:21,767 --> 00:43:22,517
OH.

580
00:43:23,400 --> 00:43:24,534
WELL...

581
00:43:26,400 --> 00:43:28,434
I ORDERED THIS
FOR YOUR BIRTHDAY.

582
00:43:28,434 --> 00:43:30,100
IT'S A LITTLE LATE,

583
00:43:30,100 --> 00:43:31,100
BUT...

584
00:43:31,100 --> 00:43:33,067
BUT LOOK.

585
00:43:33,067 --> 00:43:34,767
OH, YEAH.

586
00:43:36,534 --> 00:43:37,767
IS IT THE WRONG ONE?

587
00:43:40,734 --> 00:43:42,834
SWEETHEART...

588
00:43:42,834 --> 00:43:45,767
YOU KNOW I HAVE TO TAKE PINOCCHIO
BACK TO THE OFFICE, RIGHT?

589
00:43:45,767 --> 00:43:46,734
NO!

590
00:43:46,734 --> 00:43:47,868
HE'S NOT OURS.

591
00:43:47,868 --> 00:43:50,467
THAT'S RIGHT.
HE'S MINE.

592
00:43:50,467 --> 00:43:52,334
LOOK, THIS IS WHAT
YOU'VE BEEN ASKING FOR.

593
00:43:52,334 --> 00:43:53,868
PINOCCHIO'S
JUST VISITING.

594
00:43:53,868 --> 00:43:54,868
NO.

595
00:43:54,868 --> 00:43:56,367
FIST DADDY LEFT ME,

596
00:43:56,367 --> 00:43:58,834
NOW YOU WANT TO MAKE
PINOCCHIO LEAVE, TOO?

597
00:44:06,100 --> 00:44:07,968
YOU'D NEVER LEAVE ME,

598
00:44:07,968 --> 00:44:09,234
WOULD YOU?

599
00:44:09,234 --> 00:44:09,984
NO.

600
00:44:13,934 --> 00:44:16,400
[RUSTLING]

601
00:44:21,367 --> 00:44:22,601
OH, ALL RIGHT,

602
00:44:22,601 --> 00:44:24,067
BUT JUST
FOR TONIGHT,

603
00:44:24,067 --> 00:44:25,501
BUT DON'T TELL MOM.

604
00:44:36,534 --> 00:44:37,901
GOOD NIGHT.

605
00:44:39,968 --> 00:44:42,868
[SCHOOL BELL RINGS]

606
00:44:50,701 --> 00:44:52,400
HAVE A GOOD DAY.

607
00:45:03,501 --> 00:45:04,400
[BELL RINGS]

608
00:45:04,400 --> 00:45:06,334
O.K. TIME'S UP.
LET'S GO.

609
00:45:14,300 --> 00:45:17,267
HEY, SOPHIA, HAVE YOU
SEEN PINOCCHIO?

610
00:45:17,267 --> 00:45:19,701
ZOE TOOK HIM
TO SCHOOL.

611
00:45:19,701 --> 00:45:21,634
I THOUGHT YOU KNEW.

612
00:45:21,634 --> 00:45:22,901
DAMN.

613
00:45:22,901 --> 00:45:25,200
SHE KNEW I WANTED TO TAKE
HIM BACK TO THE OFFICE TODAY.

614
00:45:25,200 --> 00:45:26,634
OH...

615
00:45:52,667 --> 00:45:54,434
MY GOD.

616
00:45:59,367 --> 00:46:02,133
[SINGING]

617
00:46:04,734 --> 00:46:06,968
COME ON, BETH,
GIVE HIM BACK.

618
00:46:06,968 --> 00:46:08,534
GIVE HIM BACK!

619
00:46:08,534 --> 00:46:10,067
COME ON,
GIVE HIM BACK!

620
00:46:10,067 --> 00:46:11,667
GOOD ONE, BETH.

621
00:46:11,667 --> 00:46:12,701
[THUNK]

622
00:46:14,033 --> 00:46:16,334
HERE
SHE COMES.

623
00:46:16,334 --> 00:46:17,801
♪ ZOEY-BLOWY ♪

624
00:46:17,801 --> 00:46:19,868
♪ ZOEY-BLOWY ♪♪

625
00:46:23,234 --> 00:46:25,434
PINOCCHIO, WHERE ARE YOU?

626
00:46:26,868 --> 00:46:28,167
PINOCCHIO...

627
00:46:29,334 --> 00:46:30,868
THERE YOU ARE.

628
00:46:33,434 --> 00:46:35,267
PINOCCHIO.

629
00:46:35,267 --> 00:46:37,334
WHAT ARE YOU UP TO?

630
00:46:56,300 --> 00:46:59,033
BETH, WAIT UP!

631
00:47:20,400 --> 00:47:21,434
AAH!

632
00:47:29,100 --> 00:47:30,060
AAH!
AAH!

633
00:47:34,734 --> 00:47:36,767
OH, MY GOD!

634
00:47:40,968 --> 00:47:43,534
HONEY, ARE YOU ALL
RIGHT? ARE YOU O.K.?

635
00:47:43,534 --> 00:47:45,133
IS SHE ALL RIGHT?

636
00:47:45,133 --> 00:47:46,300
I THINK SH--

637
00:47:46,300 --> 00:47:47,734
I THINK
SHE'S O.K.

638
00:47:47,734 --> 00:47:49,834
SHE MAY BE IN SHOCK.

639
00:47:49,834 --> 00:47:51,400
OH, NO.
IT'S BETH.

640
00:47:51,400 --> 00:47:53,000
SHE LOOKS O.K.

641
00:47:55,367 --> 00:47:59,400
IT'S ALL RIGHT, EVERYONE.
SHE'S O.K. SHE'S FINE.

642
00:48:21,400 --> 00:48:23,234
YOU'RE A FUNNY MAN,
BARRY.

643
00:48:23,234 --> 00:48:26,767
OH, WELL, YOU SHOULD SEE ME
WITH A LAMPSHADE ON MY HEAD.

644
00:48:26,767 --> 00:48:28,167
WHAT'S UP?

645
00:48:28,167 --> 00:48:29,968
WELL, THANKS TO YOU, MY
DAUGHTER'S NOW COMPLETELY ATTACHED

646
00:48:29,968 --> 00:48:31,801
TO THAT DAMN PUPPET.

647
00:48:31,801 --> 00:48:33,501
WHAT PUPPET?

648
00:48:33,501 --> 00:48:35,033
THE ONE YOU PUT
IN MY CAR ON FRIDAY.

649
00:48:35,033 --> 00:48:36,567
PINOCCHIO?

650
00:48:36,567 --> 00:48:38,167
<i>[INTERCOM] JENNIFER,
THERE'S A DR. EDWARDS</i>

651
00:48:38,167 --> 00:48:40,467
<i>ON LINE ONE FOR YOU.</i>

652
00:48:40,467 --> 00:48:42,367
A DOCTOR?

653
00:48:42,367 --> 00:48:44,801
WHATEVER HAPPENED
TO THE GARDENER?

654
00:48:44,801 --> 00:48:46,634
LANDSCAPER.

655
00:48:46,634 --> 00:48:48,400
HELLO, DOCTOR. WHAT
CAN I DO FOR YOU?

656
00:48:48,400 --> 00:48:52,667
ZOE JUST SHOWED UP HERE
AT MY OFFICE UNANNOUNCED.

657
00:48:52,667 --> 00:48:53,901
WHAT?

658
00:48:53,901 --> 00:48:55,567
THERE WAS AN ACCIDENT
AT HER SCHOOL.

659
00:48:55,567 --> 00:48:58,467
SHE CLAIMS HER PUPPET
PUSHED ONE OF HER CLASSMATES

660
00:48:58,467 --> 00:49:00,400
IN FRONT OF A BUS.

661
00:49:00,400 --> 00:49:02,033
I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

662
00:49:05,734 --> 00:49:07,968
I'M TAKING IT BACK TO
WORK TOMORROW ANYWAY.

663
00:49:07,968 --> 00:49:10,000
I DON'T THINK
THAT'S A GOOD IDEA.

664
00:49:10,000 --> 00:49:12,467
SHE SEEMS TO HAVE FORMED
A COMPULSIVE-DEPENDENT

665
00:49:12,467 --> 00:49:14,067
ATTACHMENT TO IT.

666
00:49:14,067 --> 00:49:18,300
SEPARATION AT THIS POINT MIGHT
BE TOO TRAUMATIC FOR HER.

667
00:49:27,033 --> 00:49:30,133
ZOE, DO YOU KNOW WHAT HAPPENED
TO YOUR NEW BETTY DOLL?

668
00:49:30,133 --> 00:49:32,434
PINOCCHIO WAS JEALOUS.

669
00:49:32,434 --> 00:49:34,934
AND WHAT ABOUT
THE GIRL AT SCHOOL?

670
00:49:34,934 --> 00:49:37,234
SHE WAS PICKING ON ME.

671
00:49:37,234 --> 00:49:39,701
PINOCCHIO WAS JUST
TRYING TO PROTECT ME.

672
00:49:42,801 --> 00:49:46,067
DO YOU KNOW THAT SHE COULD
HAVE GOTTEN SERIOUSLY HURT?

673
00:49:46,067 --> 00:49:48,667
PINOCCHIO DIDN'T MEAN
TO DO A BAD THING.

674
00:49:48,667 --> 00:49:54,234
HE JUST DOESN'T UNDERSTAND THE
DIFFERENCE BETWEEN RIGHT AND WRONG.

675
00:49:58,534 --> 00:50:00,968
HOW LONG'S
IT BEEN LIKE THIS?

676
00:50:03,601 --> 00:50:05,200
EVER SINCE THE DIVORCE.

677
00:50:05,200 --> 00:50:08,367
WE'VE BEEN DRIFTING
FURTHER AND FURTHER APART.

678
00:50:08,367 --> 00:50:11,300
I JUST DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO DO ANYMORE.

679
00:50:13,534 --> 00:50:17,267
COULD YOU QUIT YOUR JOB AND
STAY HOME WITH HER FULL-TIME?

680
00:50:17,267 --> 00:50:19,067
DOES WARREN PAY ALIMONY?

681
00:50:19,067 --> 00:50:21,267
MM-MMM.
JUST CHILD SUPPORT.

682
00:50:21,267 --> 00:50:23,901
I WAS MAKING MORE MONEY THAN
HE WAS WHEN WE SEPARATED.

683
00:50:23,901 --> 00:50:26,701
THAT WAS ONE
OF THE PROBLEMS.

684
00:50:26,701 --> 00:50:29,767
WELL, YOU KNOW YOU COULD
ALWAYS MOVE IN WITH ME.

685
00:50:33,100 --> 00:50:35,067
WHY NOT?

686
00:50:35,067 --> 00:50:38,133
YOU KNOW HOW I FEEL
ABOUT YOU AND ZOE.

687
00:50:38,133 --> 00:50:39,834
I KNOW.

688
00:50:39,834 --> 00:50:40,934
I KNOW.

689
00:50:43,367 --> 00:50:45,601
I LOVE THE OFFER.

690
00:50:47,501 --> 00:50:50,968
BUT ZOE'S BEEN THROUGH
ENOUGH CHANGES FOR ONE YEAR.

691
00:50:53,934 --> 00:50:54,968
HERE.

692
00:50:56,567 --> 00:50:57,868
SPOON ME.

693
00:51:16,567 --> 00:51:17,407
[SIREN]

694
00:51:19,067 --> 00:51:21,467
LOOK,
THE BOTTOM LINE IS,

695
00:51:21,467 --> 00:51:24,467
THE DECEASED WAS A
WELL-KNOWN PUSHER AND PIMP.

696
00:51:24,467 --> 00:51:26,501
TO TELL THE TRUTH,
I DON'T SEE ANY JURY

697
00:51:26,501 --> 00:51:28,267
FEELING ANY SYMPATHY
TOWARD HIM.

698
00:51:28,267 --> 00:51:30,367
OH, GEE...

699
00:51:30,367 --> 00:51:31,400
WOW.

700
00:51:31,400 --> 00:51:33,701
UM, MAYBE THEY'LL
HAVE A CHANGE OF HEART

701
00:51:33,701 --> 00:51:35,801
WHEN THEY HEAR
HOW HE DIED.

702
00:51:38,501 --> 00:51:42,968
SEE, YOUR CLIENT, HE--HE
HUNG HIM ON A MEAT HOOK,

703
00:51:42,968 --> 00:51:46,467
AND THEN HE TORTURED HIM
TO DEATH WITH A BLOWTORCH.

704
00:51:46,467 --> 00:51:49,033
YOU KNOW, HE EVEN RECORDED
IT SO HE COULD LISTEN TO IT

705
00:51:49,033 --> 00:51:53,234
AND ENJOY IT AGAIN
AND AGAIN AND AGAIN.

706
00:51:53,234 --> 00:51:54,267
IT'S GREAT.

707
00:51:54,267 --> 00:51:55,400
HERE, TAKE A LISTEN.

708
00:51:57,434 --> 00:51:58,434
<i>AAH!</i>

709
00:51:59,634 --> 00:52:01,400
<i>AAH!</i>

710
00:52:01,400 --> 00:52:02,400
[CHUCKLING]

711
00:52:02,400 --> 00:52:04,200
<i>NO! PLEASE! GOD, NO!</i>

712
00:52:04,200 --> 00:52:05,701
OOH.

713
00:52:05,701 --> 00:52:06,968
<i>NO, PLEASE, GOD!</i>

714
00:52:06,968 --> 00:52:07,968
<i>AAH!</i>

715
00:52:07,968 --> 00:52:10,667
THAT'S GOT TO HURT.

716
00:52:10,667 --> 00:52:11,667
<i>AAH!</i>

717
00:52:13,267 --> 00:52:15,200
[CHUCKLING]

718
00:52:15,200 --> 00:52:17,000
<i>AAH!</i>

719
00:52:17,000 --> 00:52:18,000
<i>AAH!</i>

720
00:52:20,334 --> 00:52:21,567
[LAUGHING]

721
00:52:31,934 --> 00:52:34,567
[RETCHING]

722
00:52:38,000 --> 00:52:40,133
[WATER RUNNING]

723
00:52:51,934 --> 00:52:53,400
HA HA...

724
00:52:54,467 --> 00:52:56,534
AH, SO...

725
00:52:56,534 --> 00:52:57,834
DO WE DEAL

726
00:52:57,834 --> 00:53:01,200
OR DO YOU STILL
WANT TO GO TO COURT?

727
00:53:01,200 --> 00:53:04,634
I NEVER HEARD
MY CLIENT'S VOICE.

728
00:53:04,634 --> 00:53:06,167
EXCUSE ME?

729
00:53:07,734 --> 00:53:09,234
ON YOUR TAPE.

730
00:53:09,234 --> 00:53:12,434
WITHOUT HIS VOICE,
YOUR TAPE IS WORTHLESS.

731
00:53:12,434 --> 00:53:14,968
I'LL HAVE THE JUDGE
RULE IT INFLAMMATORY.

732
00:53:14,968 --> 00:53:17,033
THE JURY
WILL NEVER HEAR IT.

733
00:53:28,767 --> 00:53:31,434
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

734
00:53:33,334 --> 00:53:34,634
GARRICK RESIDENCE.

735
00:53:34,634 --> 00:53:36,767
SOPHIA, HI.
YEAH, IT'S ME.

736
00:53:36,767 --> 00:53:38,667
LISTEN, I'M
GOING TO BE LATE,

737
00:53:38,667 --> 00:53:40,567
SO DON'T HOLD
DINNER FOR ME.

738
00:53:40,567 --> 00:53:42,968
I HAVE AN APPOINTMENT AT
THE I.N.S. THIS AFTERNOON.

739
00:53:42,968 --> 00:53:45,367
REMEMBER?
TO RENEW MY WORK VISA.

740
00:53:45,367 --> 00:53:47,901
OH, JEEZ,
I COMPLETELY FORGOT.

741
00:53:47,901 --> 00:53:49,601
UM, LISTEN,
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

742
00:53:49,601 --> 00:53:52,667
I'LL CALL DAVID AND SEE
IF HE CAN BABYSIT.

743
00:53:52,667 --> 00:53:54,033
O.K., THANKS.

744
00:53:58,634 --> 00:54:00,934
KAMINSKY'S LANDSCAPING.

745
00:54:00,934 --> 00:54:02,501
HEY. IT'S ME.

746
00:54:02,501 --> 00:54:05,834
LISTEN, I NEED YOU
TO DO ME A BIG FAVOR.

747
00:54:32,033 --> 00:54:34,334
SO AFTER YOU STOLE
HIS HEROIN,

748
00:54:34,334 --> 00:54:36,200
YOU SOLD IT ON THE
STREET YOURSELF?

749
00:54:36,200 --> 00:54:38,767
NO, MAN. I GAVE IT AWAY
TO THE POOR AND NEEDY,

750
00:54:38,767 --> 00:54:40,667
JUST LIKE ROBIN HOOD.

751
00:54:40,667 --> 00:54:42,501
BUT THE STUFF
WAS UNCUT.

752
00:54:42,501 --> 00:54:44,467
THREE PEOPLE DIED
OF AN OVERDOSE.

753
00:54:44,467 --> 00:54:47,767
HEY, THAT'S WHAT
THE BOX WANTED.

754
00:54:47,767 --> 00:54:49,133
THE BOX?

755
00:54:50,400 --> 00:54:51,367
YEAH.

756
00:54:51,367 --> 00:54:54,567
YOU KNOW,
THE TELEVISION.

757
00:54:54,567 --> 00:54:56,167
IT TOLD ME TO--

758
00:54:56,167 --> 00:54:59,400
IT TOLD ME TO KILL HIM
AND HAND OUT HIS STUFF.

759
00:54:59,400 --> 00:55:03,667
THE TELEVISION TOLD
YOU TO KILL THE PUSHER?

760
00:55:03,667 --> 00:55:05,000
DAMN STRAIGHT.

761
00:55:05,000 --> 00:55:07,267
I WOULDN'T HAVE
DONE IT OTHERWISE.

762
00:55:07,267 --> 00:55:08,701
I LIKED THE GUY.

763
00:55:08,701 --> 00:55:13,100
DO YOU MEAN YOU SAW A SHOW
ON VIGILANTES OR SOMETHING?

764
00:55:13,100 --> 00:55:13,850
NO.

765
00:55:14,534 --> 00:55:16,534
IT WASN'T NO DAMN SHOW.

766
00:55:16,534 --> 00:55:19,167
THE BOX WASN'T EVEN ON.

767
00:55:23,934 --> 00:55:25,601
ALL RIGHT.

768
00:55:33,100 --> 00:55:35,901
I'M NOT CRAZY, LADY.

769
00:55:35,901 --> 00:55:38,334
THE BOX DID TALK TO ME.

770
00:55:47,701 --> 00:55:49,901
IT'S BEDTIME,
SWEETHEART.

771
00:55:49,901 --> 00:55:51,033
GOOD NIGHT.

772
00:55:51,033 --> 00:55:54,100
DO YOU WANT ME
TO COME TUCK YOU IN?

773
00:55:54,100 --> 00:55:55,167
NO, THANKS.

774
00:56:08,501 --> 00:56:10,534
[ZOE]
STOP PLAYING AROUND NOW.

775
00:56:10,534 --> 00:56:12,634
WE HAVE TO GO TO BED.

776
00:56:12,634 --> 00:56:16,801
I'M THE ONE WHO IS GETTING
INTO TROUBLE, O.K.?

777
00:56:16,801 --> 00:56:19,968
ZOE...ARE YOU TALKING
TO SOMEONE IN THERE?

778
00:56:19,968 --> 00:56:22,067
JUST PINOCCHIO.

779
00:56:23,601 --> 00:56:25,834
OH...O.K.

780
00:56:28,133 --> 00:56:31,734
ZOE, YOU SHOULDN'T
TELL PEOPLE I TALK TO YOU.

781
00:56:31,734 --> 00:56:32,734
WHY NOT?

782
00:56:32,734 --> 00:56:34,734
BECAUSE THEY'LL
TAKE ME AWAY FROM YOU.

783
00:56:34,734 --> 00:56:36,801
THEN I'LL NEVER
GET TO BE A REAL BOY

784
00:56:36,801 --> 00:56:38,334
AND BE YOUR BROTHER.

785
00:56:38,334 --> 00:56:41,434
YOU REALLY THINK WE'LL
BE A FAMILY SOMEDAY--

786
00:56:41,434 --> 00:56:43,501
YOU, ME, AND MOM?

787
00:56:43,501 --> 00:56:46,567
<i>SURE. YOU KNOW
I'LL NEVER LEAVE YOU.</i>

788
00:56:46,567 --> 00:56:49,067
BUT WE CAN'T BE
TOO SURE ABOUT MOM...

789
00:56:49,067 --> 00:56:51,267
NOT AS LONG AS
DAVID'S AROUND.

790
00:56:51,267 --> 00:56:52,834
I KNOW.

791
00:56:52,834 --> 00:56:55,334
I CAN MAKE DAVID GO AWAY.

792
00:56:55,334 --> 00:56:57,234
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

793
00:57:03,834 --> 00:57:05,200
PINOCCHIO.

794
00:57:05,200 --> 00:57:07,734
REMEMBER, YOU CAN'T
BECOME A REAL BOY

795
00:57:07,734 --> 00:57:09,934
IF YOU KEEP
DOING BAD THINGS.

796
00:57:09,934 --> 00:57:12,501
GETTING RID OF DAVID
WOULD BE A GOOD THING,

797
00:57:12,501 --> 00:57:16,467
THE SAME WAY PUNISHING THAT
BITCH AT SCHOOL WAS A GOOD THING.

798
00:57:28,200 --> 00:57:30,234
[FOOTSTEPS]

799
00:57:35,434 --> 00:57:36,567
PINOCCHIO.

800
00:57:39,133 --> 00:57:41,234
WHERE ARE YOU?

801
00:57:44,334 --> 00:57:46,033
[FOOTSTEPS]

802
00:58:12,834 --> 00:58:13,834
ZOE!

803
00:58:13,834 --> 00:58:14,868
[GASP]

804
00:58:16,400 --> 00:58:18,934
WHAT ARE YOU DOING UP?

805
00:58:18,934 --> 00:58:20,400
GETTING PINOCCHIO.

806
00:58:20,400 --> 00:58:22,868
I THOUGHT
HE WAS IN YOUR ROOM.

807
00:58:22,868 --> 00:58:24,868
NO. HE'S IN
THE BASEMENT.

808
00:58:24,868 --> 00:58:26,400
WHOA. I'LL GET HIM.

809
00:58:26,400 --> 00:58:28,133
YOU GO TO BED.

810
00:58:28,133 --> 00:58:29,634
NO. THAT'S O.K.

811
00:58:29,634 --> 00:58:31,400
I'LL GET HIM.

812
00:58:31,400 --> 00:58:34,901
NO. IF YOUR MOTHER
COMES HOME, FINDS YOU UP,

813
00:58:34,901 --> 00:58:36,934
SHE'S GOING TO KILL ME.

814
00:58:36,934 --> 00:58:38,968
GO TO BED.

815
00:58:40,267 --> 00:58:41,300
GO ON.

816
00:58:42,234 --> 00:58:44,167
I'LL GET HIM.

817
00:59:22,534 --> 00:59:23,567
O.K.

818
00:59:25,234 --> 00:59:26,234
VERY FUNNY.

819
00:59:26,234 --> 00:59:28,934
GET BACK TO BED, ZOE!

820
00:59:28,934 --> 00:59:32,033
GOD--DAMN IT!

821
00:59:34,467 --> 00:59:37,968
O.K., ZOE. HERE I COME.

822
00:59:37,968 --> 00:59:40,434
YOU BETTER GET TO BED.

823
00:59:42,634 --> 00:59:43,667
UNH!

824
01:00:01,534 --> 01:00:03,200
[DOOR CREAKING]

825
01:00:05,601 --> 01:00:08,200
[DOOR CLOSES]

826
01:00:10,834 --> 01:00:12,100
EXCUSE ME, I NEED--

827
01:00:12,100 --> 01:00:13,267
MOMMY!

828
01:00:13,267 --> 01:00:15,033
ZOE!

829
01:00:17,501 --> 01:00:19,000
ARE YOU O.K.?

830
01:00:19,000 --> 01:00:20,334
[CRYING]

831
01:00:20,334 --> 01:00:22,400
OH, MOMMY, IT'S DAVID!

832
01:00:22,400 --> 01:00:23,467
WHAT HAPPENED?

833
01:00:23,467 --> 01:00:25,501
LOOKS LIKE YOUR FRIEND
TOOK A NASTY TUMBLE

834
01:00:25,501 --> 01:00:27,300
DOWN THE BASEMENT STEPS.

835
01:00:27,300 --> 01:00:28,734
IS HE O.K.?

836
01:00:28,734 --> 01:00:30,300
WE'VE NOTIFIED
HIS PARENTS.

837
01:00:30,300 --> 01:00:32,067
IF YOUR DAUGHTER
HADN'T DIALED 911,

838
01:00:32,067 --> 01:00:34,934
I DON'T THINK
HE WOULD HAVE MADE IT.

839
01:00:34,934 --> 01:00:36,300
[SIREN]

840
01:00:36,300 --> 01:00:37,667
O.K.

841
01:00:37,667 --> 01:00:39,100
ALL RIGHT.

842
01:00:44,400 --> 01:00:47,567
PINOCCHIO, DID YOU MAKE
DAVID FALL DOWN THOSE STAIRS?

843
01:00:51,734 --> 01:00:53,234
ANSWER ME!

844
01:00:53,234 --> 01:00:56,167
DID YOU MAKE DAVID
FALL DOWN THOSE STAIRS?

845
01:00:56,167 --> 01:00:57,434
NO.

846
01:01:05,067 --> 01:01:06,968
YOU'RE LYING,
AREN'T YOU?

847
01:01:06,968 --> 01:01:11,534
YOU KNOW, MOM WOULD HAVE TO
SPEND A LOT MORE TIME WITH US

848
01:01:11,534 --> 01:01:14,434
IF SOPHIA WASN'T AROUND.

849
01:01:24,100 --> 01:01:25,601
ZOE?

850
01:01:25,601 --> 01:01:27,467
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

851
01:01:27,467 --> 01:01:28,767
GETTING BUGS.

852
01:01:28,767 --> 01:01:30,334
I FORGOT.

853
01:01:30,334 --> 01:01:32,834
I HAD TO BRING ONE
FOR SCIENCE TODAY.

854
01:01:32,834 --> 01:01:35,300
I THOUGHT YOU MIGHT WANT TO
STAY HOME FROM SCHOOL TODAY.

855
01:01:35,300 --> 01:01:37,767
NO. I'M O.K.

856
01:01:37,767 --> 01:01:39,934
YOU SURE? REALLY?

857
01:01:39,934 --> 01:01:41,801
REALLY.

858
01:01:41,801 --> 01:01:42,834
O.K.

859
01:01:44,000 --> 01:01:45,634
MMM. HAVE A GOOD DAY.

860
01:01:56,767 --> 01:01:58,133
[ENGINE STARTS]

861
01:02:04,834 --> 01:02:06,367
ZOE.

862
01:02:07,567 --> 01:02:09,601
I FOUND WALTER
IN THE TRASH.

863
01:02:09,601 --> 01:02:11,367
DID YOU THROW HIM AWAY?

864
01:02:14,601 --> 01:02:16,100
WHAT HAVE YOU GOT THERE?

865
01:02:18,067 --> 01:02:19,567
[CRICKET CHIRPING]

866
01:02:19,567 --> 01:02:21,834
A CONSCIENCE
FOR PINOCCHIO.

867
01:02:21,834 --> 01:02:24,100
SO HE WON'T DO
ANY MORE BAD THINGS.

868
01:02:26,667 --> 01:02:28,868
WELL...GOOD LUCK.

869
01:02:28,868 --> 01:02:32,467
IN THE ORIGINAL
ITALIAN VERSION,

870
01:02:32,467 --> 01:02:36,133
PINOCCHIO ACTUALLY
HAD A VERY BAD TEMPER,

871
01:02:36,133 --> 01:02:41,801
AND HE SQUASHED THE CRICKET
DURING ONE OF HIS TANTRUMS.

872
01:02:41,801 --> 01:02:43,767
COME ON.

873
01:02:48,868 --> 01:02:51,834
DO YOU WANT TO TELL ME
ABOUT DAVID'S ACCIDENT?

874
01:02:51,834 --> 01:02:54,767
YOUR MOTHER SAYS THAT HE
WAS VERY SERIOUSLY HURT.

875
01:02:54,767 --> 01:02:57,367
YOU MUST HAVE SOME
FEELINGS ABOUT THAT.

876
01:02:58,767 --> 01:03:00,968
<i>[INTERCOM BEEPS]
DR. EDWARDS?</i>

877
01:03:00,968 --> 01:03:02,868
I'M WITH A PATIENT,
KELLY.

878
01:03:02,868 --> 01:03:05,067
<i>I KNOW, BUT YOU SAID YOU
WANTED TO PERSONALLY SPEAK</i>

879
01:03:05,067 --> 01:03:06,968
<i>TO THE DELIVERY MAN
WHEN HE GOT HERE.</i>

880
01:03:06,968 --> 01:03:08,501
OH, RIGHT.
THANK YOU.

881
01:03:08,501 --> 01:03:09,501
[BEEP]

882
01:03:09,501 --> 01:03:10,601
EXCUSE ME, ZOE.

883
01:03:10,601 --> 01:03:11,934
I'LL BE BACK
IN A MINUTE.

884
01:03:21,901 --> 01:03:23,434
I HOPE YOU'RE HAPPY.

885
01:03:23,434 --> 01:03:26,200
<i>NOW HE THINKS
I HURT DAVID.</i>

886
01:03:26,200 --> 01:03:28,434
ARE YOU SURE YOU DIDN'T?

887
01:03:28,434 --> 01:03:29,734
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

888
01:03:29,734 --> 01:03:30,801
YOU KNOW.

889
01:03:30,801 --> 01:03:32,234
NO, I DON'T!

890
01:03:32,234 --> 01:03:34,400
YOU'RE THE ONE WHO SLAMMED
THE DOOR IN HIS FACE.

891
01:03:34,400 --> 01:03:35,501
ARE YOU SURE?

892
01:03:35,501 --> 01:03:37,400
WHO ELSE COULD IT
HAVE BEEN?

893
01:03:37,400 --> 01:03:38,934
WHO DO YOU THINK?

894
01:03:38,934 --> 01:03:40,234
OH, NO.
IT WASN'T ME.

895
01:03:40,234 --> 01:03:41,534
IT WAS YOU.

896
01:03:41,534 --> 01:03:42,534
HOW DO YOU KNOW?

897
01:03:42,534 --> 01:03:44,267
SHUT UP.

898
01:03:44,267 --> 01:03:45,300
DID YOU SEE ME?

899
01:03:45,300 --> 01:03:46,734
SHUT UP!

900
01:03:46,734 --> 01:03:49,400
IF YOU WEREN'T THERE, HOW
CAN YOU BE SO SURE IT WAS ME?

901
01:03:49,400 --> 01:03:51,868
SHUT UP! SHUT UP!
SHUT UP! SHUT UP!

902
01:04:02,400 --> 01:04:03,834
YES, HI.

903
01:04:03,834 --> 01:04:06,367
I'D LIKE TO CHECK ON THE
CONDITION OF ONE OF YOUR PATIENTS.

904
01:04:06,367 --> 01:04:07,701
THE PATIENT'S NAME,
PLEASE?

905
01:04:07,701 --> 01:04:08,634
DAVID KAMINSKY.

906
01:04:08,634 --> 01:04:10,033
HE'S BEEN UPGRADED
TO STABLE.

907
01:04:10,033 --> 01:04:11,133
OH, HE IS?

908
01:04:11,133 --> 01:04:12,701
OH, THAT'S
WONDERFUL.

909
01:04:12,701 --> 01:04:13,634
[BEEP]

910
01:04:13,634 --> 01:04:15,167
OH, SHOOT. THAT'S
MY OTHER LINE.

911
01:04:15,167 --> 01:04:16,467
HOLD ON--
ACTUALLY, WAIT.

912
01:04:16,467 --> 01:04:17,601
JUST TELL ME,

913
01:04:17,601 --> 01:04:19,567
WHAT TIME DO VISITING
HOURS START TOMORROW?

914
01:04:19,567 --> 01:04:21,067
8 A.M.

915
01:04:21,067 --> 01:04:22,067
GREAT. THANKS.

916
01:04:22,067 --> 01:04:23,067
[BEEP]

917
01:04:23,067 --> 01:04:24,033
HELLO?

918
01:04:24,033 --> 01:04:25,567
[DR. EDWARDS]
MRS. GARRICK?

919
01:04:25,567 --> 01:04:27,033
DR. EDWARDS, HI.

920
01:04:27,033 --> 01:04:28,133
COULD YOU COME BY
MY OFFICE TOMORROW?

921
01:04:28,133 --> 01:04:29,100
TOMORROW?

922
01:04:29,100 --> 01:04:31,067
WELL , ACTUALLY I HAVE
A FULL CASELOAD,

923
01:04:31,067 --> 01:04:33,501
AND I WAS GOING TO GO TO
THE HOSPITAL TO VISIT DAVID.

924
01:04:33,501 --> 01:04:34,734
WELL, THIS
IS IMPORTANT.

925
01:04:34,734 --> 01:04:36,067
WELL, IF THERE'S
SOMETHING WRONG,

926
01:04:36,067 --> 01:04:37,200
I'D LIKE
TO KNOW NOW.

927
01:04:37,200 --> 01:04:40,667
WELL, I'D REALLY LIKE
TO DO THIS IN PERSON.

928
01:04:40,667 --> 01:04:42,701
[SIGHS]

929
01:04:44,167 --> 01:04:45,300
ALL RIGHT.

930
01:04:45,300 --> 01:04:47,334
I SUPPOSE I CAN
REARRANGE A FEW THINGS

931
01:04:47,334 --> 01:04:49,267
AND GO SEE DAVID
TOMORROW NIGHT.

932
01:04:49,267 --> 01:04:51,367
I'M GOING TO HAVE TO
STOP BY YOUR OFFICE

933
01:04:51,367 --> 01:04:52,868
ON MY WAY TO WORK.

934
01:04:52,868 --> 01:04:54,367
WILL YOU BE IN
THAT EARLY?

935
01:04:54,367 --> 01:04:55,300
O.K. GOOD.

936
01:04:55,300 --> 01:04:58,367
ALL RIGHT. WELL,
I'LL SEE YOU THEN.

937
01:04:58,367 --> 01:05:00,300
GOOD NIGHT.

938
01:05:05,267 --> 01:05:08,767
NOW YOU'VE DONE IT.

939
01:05:08,767 --> 01:05:11,234
IF DAVID TELLS MOM
HE WAS PUSHED,

940
01:05:11,234 --> 01:05:13,300
SHE'S GOING
TO HAVE ME PUT AWAY.

941
01:05:13,300 --> 01:05:15,300
I COULD TALK TO HIM
FOR YOU.

942
01:05:15,300 --> 01:05:17,234
ADMIT THAT
IT WAS ME, NOT YOU.

943
01:05:17,234 --> 01:05:19,133
YOU'D DO THAT
FOR ME?

944
01:05:19,133 --> 01:05:20,667
YOU'RE MY SISTER,
AREN'T YOU?

945
01:05:20,667 --> 01:05:21,734
WE'RE FAMILY.

946
01:05:21,734 --> 01:05:23,734
BUT HOW?

947
01:05:23,734 --> 01:05:25,467
GIVE ME LIFE.

948
01:05:25,467 --> 01:05:26,434
ME?

949
01:05:26,434 --> 01:05:28,467
YOU HAVE
THE POWER, ZOE.

950
01:05:28,467 --> 01:05:30,434
YOU ARE THE BLUE FAIRY.

951
01:05:32,100 --> 01:05:33,801
WHAT DO I HAVE TO DO?

952
01:05:33,801 --> 01:05:36,534
CUT MY STRINGS.

953
01:05:42,467 --> 01:05:44,133
YOU PROMISE TO BE GOOD?

954
01:05:44,133 --> 01:05:45,601
I PROMISE.

955
01:05:51,534 --> 01:05:53,033
YOU PROMISE TO BE GOOD?

956
01:05:53,033 --> 01:05:55,567
I PROMISE!

957
01:05:55,567 --> 01:05:57,234
[SNIP]

958
01:05:57,234 --> 01:05:58,567
[SNIP]

959
01:05:58,567 --> 01:05:59,601
[SNIP]

960
01:06:03,200 --> 01:06:05,734
I'M FREE! FREE!

961
01:06:05,734 --> 01:06:07,200
COME ON!

962
01:06:07,200 --> 01:06:09,734
LET'S GO SEE DAVID.

963
01:06:09,734 --> 01:06:10,834
[DOOR OPENS]

964
01:06:57,734 --> 01:07:00,968
PINOCCHIO, WAIT FOR ME!

965
01:07:15,934 --> 01:07:18,434
OVER HERE, ZOE!

966
01:07:18,434 --> 01:07:20,200
THIS WAY!

967
01:07:36,868 --> 01:07:38,734
PINOCCHIO?

968
01:07:38,734 --> 01:07:41,167
PINOCCHIO, WHERE ARE YOU?

969
01:07:45,367 --> 01:07:46,801
PINOCCHIO!

970
01:07:46,801 --> 01:07:47,901
PINOCCHIO!

971
01:07:49,100 --> 01:07:50,934
PINOCCHIO!

972
01:08:23,834 --> 01:08:26,868
[MONITOR BEEPING]

973
01:08:40,834 --> 01:08:42,868
[ALARM BEEPS]

974
01:09:23,834 --> 01:09:24,554
[RING]

